### MongoDB Demo API - Error Handling and Edge Cases
### Base URL: http://localhost:3001

### Test 404 - Non-existent Route
GET http://localhost:3001/api/nonexistent
Accept: application/json

###

### Test 404 - Non-existent Query ID
GET http://localhost:3001/api/queries/nonexistent-query
Accept: application/json

###

### Test 404 - Non-existent Predefined Query Execution
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute/nonexistent-query
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Test 400 - Custom Query Missing Collection
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute-custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "find",
  "query": {}
}

###

### Test 400 - Custom Query Missing Query
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute-custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "collection": "users",
  "operation": "find"
}

###

### Test 400 - Invalid Collection Name
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute-custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "collection": "invalidcollection",
  "operation": "find",
  "query": {}
}

###

### Test 403 - Forbidden Operation (Insert)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute-custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "collection": "users",
  "operation": "insertOne",
  "query": {
    "name": "Test User"
  }
}

###

### Test 403 - Forbidden Operation (Update)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute-custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "collection": "users",
  "operation": "updateOne",
  "query": {
    "filter": { "_id": "someId" },
    "update": { "$set": { "name": "Updated Name" } }
  }
}

###

### Test 403 - Forbidden Operation (Delete)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute-custom
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "collection": "users",
  "operation": "deleteOne",
  "query": {
    "_id": "someId"
  }
}

###

### Test Invalid JSON Body
POST http://localhost:3001/api/data/execute/basic-find-companies
